Below is an example of a QRScanner implementation using the react-native-camera library. This library has a built-in QR code scanning functionality.

```javascript
// First, import React and Component from react
import React, { Component } from 'react';
// Import the react-native-camera package
import { RNCamera } from 'react-native-camera';

export default class QRScanner extends Component {
    // Define the method to handle QR code detection
    barcodeRecognized = ({ barcodes }) => {
        // Fetch the barcode data from the first barcode detected
        const barcodeData = barcodes[0].data;

        // Call the onSuccess callback prop with the barcode data
        this.props.onSuccess(barcodeData);
    };

    // Here is our render method, which returns our camera component
    render() {
        return (
            <RNCamera
                // Set the camera's aspect ratio
                aspect={RNCamera.constants.Aspect.fill}
                // Enable barcode scanning
                onBarCodeRead={this.barcodeRecognized}
                // Set the camera type to back
                type={RNCamera.constants.Type.back}
                // You can set flash mode to auto, on, off or torch
                flashMode={RNCamera.constants.FlashMode.auto}
                // Capture audio along with video
                captureAudio={false}
                // Style to stretch the camera component to full screen.
                style={{flex: 1}}
                // Catch any errors (like if the user doesn't grant permissions)
                onError={this.props.onError}
            />
        );
    }
}
```
This QRScanner component will take two callback functions as props: onSuccess and onError. When a QR code is detected, the onSuccess function will be called with the value of the QR code. If there is an error (like if the user doesn't grant camera permissions), the onError function will be called.

In order to use this QRScanner component, install react-native-camera via npm: 
```npm install react-native-camera --save``` 

Then you can use the QRScanner component as follow:
```javascript
<QRScanner 
    onSuccess={(data) => console.log(data)} 
    onError={(error) => console.log(error)}
/>
```

Remember to request camera permission. You can refer to [react-native camera documentation](https://react-native-camera.github.io/react-native-camera/docs/installation) for more information.

